"content": "<p>Stories that are made up and which are contrary to right doctrine or holy living.</p>\n<h2>Some prefer myths to truth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:3-2Tim4:4\">2TI 4:3–4:4</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Myths are harmful to the body of Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:3-1Tim1:4\">1TI 1:3–1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:6-1Tim4:8\">1TI 4:6–4:8</a></p>\n<h2>Sound teaching by God's servants dispels myths</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:13-Titus1:14\">TIT 1:13–1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1-1Tim4:6\">1TI 4:1–4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:9-Titus1:11\">TIT 1:9–1:11</a></p>",
